            <title>[FLINK-12216] Respect the number of bytes from input parameters in HybridMemorySegment</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-12216</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For the following two methods in HybridMemorySegment class,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public final void get(int offset, ByteBuffer target, int numBytes)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public final void put(int offset, ByteBuffer source, int numBytes)&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the actual number of bytes read/written should be specified by the input parameter numBytes, but it does not for some types of ByteBuffer. Instead, it simply read/write until the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this is a bug and I am going to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
